ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Participant completed an intervention onboarding call (applies to participants in health coach delivered cognitive behavioral therapy (CBT) intervention and Online CBT program arms)
Participant registered/set up their account for the painTRAINER program (applies to participants in Online CBT program only)
Number of intervention sessions completed during the one-year study period (from day 0 to day 410)
Number of intervention sessions completed during the intended study treatment period (from day 0 to day 105)
Session 1 completion as number of days from randomization date
Notes: Number of days from randomization date

ElementDescription: Session 2 completion as number of days from randomization date
Notes: Number of days from randomization date

ElementDescription: Session 3 completion as number of days from randomization date
Notes: Number of days from randomization date

ElementDescription: Session 4 completion as number of days from randomization date
Notes: Number of days from randomization date

ElementDescription: Session 5 completion as number of days from randomization date
Notes: Number of days from randomization date

ElementDescription: Session 6 completion as number of days from randomization date
Notes: Number of days from randomization date

ElementDescription: Session 7 completion as number of days from randomization date
Notes: Number of days from randomization date

ElementDescription: Session 8 completion as number of days from randomization date
Notes: Number of days from randomization date

ElementDescription: Participant requested to stop intervention activities or intervention staff stopped active outreach to participant during the treatment period because maximum contact attempts were fulfilled without successful engagement
Number of days from randomization date to date stopped intervention activities or active intervention outreach to participant during the treatment period
Notes: Number of days from randomization date

ElementDescription: Reason for stopping intervention activities or active intervention outreach to participant during the treatment period
Notes: 0 = No reason given; 1 = Dealing with other health or life issues; 2 = Does not have time; 3 = Does not like intervention services; 4 = Intervention is not improving pain; 5 = Not interested; 6 = Privacy concerns; 7 = Unable to reach/maximum contact attempts fulfilled
